					<div class="commentheading">On November 18, 2006 at 07:52 PM, jen (guest) said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody">I experimented with ganache to frost some cakes over the summer.  I was hoping for it to be pourable.  I started with 300g or dark chocolate, a small pat of butter and 1 cup of cream.  it was not pourable, so I tried another half cup of milk, and to my surprise, it was thicker, so I ended up spreading.<br />
<br />
it wasn't the look I was going for, but it was delicious.  it retained the dark chocolate taste, even with all the cream, but it was lighter, more delicate.<br />
<br />
Perhaps since I had more liquid, the chocolate melted more easily, but I found fairly coars pieces of broken chocolate had no problem melting.</div>
