					<div class="commentheading">On December 20, 2008 at 09:42 PM, Michael Chu said...</div>
					<div class="commentsubject"></div>
					<div class="commentbody"><div class='commentquote'>MB wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>If I'm going to make the truffles using milk chocolate, do I need to adjust the amount of cream used? </div></div><br />
You'll will probably need to adjust the cream or else the ganache won't set properly. I would suggest not using milk chocolate - the flavor is already tempered with the cream so it won't taste like bitter dark chocolate.<br />
<br />
<div class='commentquote'>Anonymous wrote:<div class='commentquotebody'>Also, the "cocoa" dusting, is that unsweetened cocoa?</div></div><br />
I've used both sweetened and unsweetened cocoa powder. I personally prefer the unsweetened, but it's up to individual taste. Both taste good.</div>
